<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-WFKA3PhINWcnNaXmt-i2vw" name=",_7CAfsKM0EeC6tIhMGJuAIA" guid="-WFKA3PhINWcnNaXmt-i2vw" changeDate="2011-08-24T05:16:52.021-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The hardware-software interface specification initiated in ISO26262-4: Clause7 shall be detailed down to a level&#xD;
    allowing the correct control and usage of hardware, and shall describe each safety-related dependency between hardware&#xD;
    and software.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It should be noted that this task requires good communication with the HW development team.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If using a model based approach then the interfaces would be a further refinement of the handoff from the systems model&#xD;
    and further analysis of the safety requirements. This information can be derived directly from the model using the&#xD;
    appropriate templates and modeling techniques.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To&amp;nbsp;specify how the HW and SW communicate and integrate with one another.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
